
==========================================================================================================================

Files in this folder:

1. iasproc.c
Runs the stored program from givem offset. The sequence is fetch, decode and execute.
2. iasproc.h
Data structures with bit fields and packed alignment to avoid padding, so that read and write is compact.
Defines the processor structures.
3. storprog.c
Defines helper function to allow user to load given program in processor memory.
4. storprog.h
Header with function prototype for helper function in (3).
5. utils.c
Defines debug functions for printing memory contents as just data or instruction content.
6. utils.h
Header with function prototypes for helper functions in (5).
7. main.c
Executes sequence of loading program (currently hardcoded), and running program using (3) and (1) respectively.

==========================================================================================================================

Compilation:

$ gcc -Wall -o iasproc iasproc.c storprog.c utils.c main.c

==========================================================================================================================

Demo of currently hardcoded program that doubles the memory contents are memory[1024] and loads it to memory[1025]:

$ ./iasproc 
Instruction area:
[05][40][01][40][00]
[00][00][02][14][01]
[00][00][00][00][00]
Data area:
[02][BB][CC][DD][EE]
[00][00][00][00][00]
MBR [540014000]
IR [5]
MAR [400]
IBR [14000]
MBR [21401]
IR [0]
Data:
[05][77][99][BB][DC]
Next program offset is [120]
$

